The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, December 25, 2002  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, Dec. 24: Mauritius-based Covanta Energy Indias Rs 20-crore proposal for issuance of fresh shares in Great Eastern Energy Corp was among the 22 foreign direct investment (FDI) proposals worth Rs 46 crore approved by the government. The proposals were cleared by commerce and industry minister Arun Shourie on the recommendations of the FIPB. 																								 New Delhi, Dec. 24: Low growth in coal and petroleum refinery products during November led to a marginal decline in the overall growth of six infrastructure industries to 3.4 per cent compared with 4 per cent in the corresponding period last year.																								 Mumbai, Dec. 24: An RBI-constituted sub-committee has prepared a standardised checklist to facilitate conduct of computer audit in banks. 																								 Calcutta, Dec. 24: A Calcutta court today rejected the bail applications of former CSE president Dinesh Singhania, former SHCIL MD B. V. Goud, and IndusInd Bank vice-president S. N. Paul, and extended their judicial custody till January 7.																								 Mumbai, Dec. 24: Birla Sun Life Insurance has augmented its capital by Rs 30 crore to Rs 180 crore.
